fields.value: Expected Outcomes for Drinking (CAPS-EXPECT CAPS-EXPECTAN CAPS-EXPEVAL CAPS-DRKCOST and CAPS-DRNKCOL2 modules)

dsDescriptionValue.value:
This unit was developed by James and Beverly Wiggins to measure R's expected outcomes for drinking 6 or more drinks on a single occasion. It asks Rs to indicate the probability that 16 outcomes will occur. It also asks Rs how much they would like some of the outcomes, how much they like the taste of various kinds of alcoholic drinks, to describe the feelings they associate (or imagine to be associated with) being drunk, how much money they spent on alcohol in the past 7 days, and how much mon ey they borrowed from others to spend on alcohol in the past 7 days.

The unit contains parts of 3 units administered to CAPS/86 respondents... EXPECTAN, EXPEVAL, and DRNKCOST. In CAPS/85 similar questions are part of DRNKCOL2.

No standard scoring.
